
Overview of noun utopia

The noun utopia has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (15) Utopia -- (a book written by Sir Thomas More (1516) describing the perfect society on an imaginary island)
2. utopia -- (ideally perfect state; especially in its social and political and moral aspects)
3. utopia -- (a work of fiction describing a utopia)
4. Utopia, Zion, Sion -- (an imaginary place considered to be perfect or ideal)
